President Obama has named Stephanie Cutter as Assistant to the President for Special Projects. In this role, Cutter will advise on key presidential initiatives, particularly in the area of communications and outreach for the implementation of health insurance reform. Cutter has extensive experience in public service, including serving as an advisor to the First Lady and as Adviser to the President in overseeing the strategy for the successful nomination of Supreme Court Justice Sonia Sotomayor. She has also worked in the Clinton Administration and held positions with various political figures. Cutter is the founder of The Cutter Media Group, LLC, and has served as a lecturer at Harvard University's John F. Kennedy School of Government.